The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for human pose estimation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on improving accuracy for extreme and wild motions suggests a potential fit for graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed method for using pre-trained models without performing the training procedure aligns with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
